Contributor Patch Policy

RVEPRTY welcomes bug fix contributions from the community via pull requests,
subject to the following conditions:

1. Scope. Contributions must be limited to bug fixes, security patches, and
   corrections to existing functionality. Pull requests that add new features,
   alter the architecture, or expand the scope of the Licensed Work are not
   covered by this policy and require a separate written agreement with RVEPRTY.

2. License Grant. By submitting a pull request, the contributor irrevocably
   grants RVEPRTY a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license
   to use, reproduce, modify, distribute, and sublicense the contributed code
   as part of the Licensed Work under any license RVEPRTY chooses, including
   this License or any future license.

3. Ownership. All intellectual property rights in accepted contributions are
   assigned to and remain the property of RVEPRTY. Contributors retain no
   ownership claim over merged patches.

4. No Distribution Rights. Submitting a patch does not grant the contributor
   any additional rights to copy, distribute, or use the Licensed Work beyond
   what this License already permits.

5. Acceptance. RVEPRTY reserves the right to accept, reject, or modify any
   submitted contribution at its sole discretion. Submission of a pull request
   does not guarantee acceptance or any obligation on the part of RVEPRTY.

6. Representation. By submitting a contribution, the contributor represents
   that they are the original author of the patch, that they have the right to
   grant the above license, and that the contribution does not infringe any
   third-party intellectual property rights.

